== Session format

- *1 hour* — lecture with live questions and estimation exercises
- *30 minutes* — instructor-led lab on a real dataset
- 14 sessions across 4 days

== Course overview

- *Day 1* — Foundations: distributed systems, MapReduce, data modeling, cost reasoning
- *Day 2* — Storage formats, Spark query execution internals
- *Day 3* — Flink stream processing, ClickHouse analytics, pipeline theory
- *Day 4* — Probabilistic data structures, differential dataflow, project briefing

== Evaluation

- 100% project presentation (separate day)
- Pick a dataset, build a system, defend your architectural choices
- No exam — your understanding shows in what you build and what you can explain

== Day 1 — Foundations & Data Modeling

+ Introduction & Motivation
+ Distributed Systems Fundamentals
+ Batch Processing: MapReduce & Beyond
+ Data Modeling at Scale
+ Cost Modeling & Performance Reasoning
